Vivien joined the Wallace group in London in 2018. His research, funded by Oxford Nanopore Technologies, explore nanopore sensing via Interferometric Scattering (iSCAT) microscopy.</p>

<p>Vivien defended his PhD at Charles Sadron Institute in Strasbourg in 2017 on the lipid membrane interactions with self-assembling cell-penetrating peptides; under the supervision of Dr Carlos Marques. He made a first postdoc on the membrane-saccharide interaction with Dr Fabrice Thalmann and Dr Carlos Marques. Vivien is a certified Physics and Chemistry high-school teacher in France (CAPES).</p>
